commentBody:
@Maverator 

Brilliant!

I really wish it had been.

@Steve L 

Luckily, I don't have encyclopedic knowledge of these things, and can be in blissful ignorance of all the things that it *might* be.  

My imagination seems to only work out answers one at a time.  If it's wrong, it'll be a while before another one occurs to me.

@Francis 

I haven't done the puzzle yet and I haven't read any of the comments but I was looking to see if you were out here yet... I tried to leave you two messages to Thursday night's puzzle, replying to your comment, and the emus just won't let them by. I don't know why. I'm not saying anything naughty at all. Although I guess that's a highly subjective subject.  ☺️

Anyhow, I'll be back after I do Friday's puzzle tomorrow / Friday.

@Francis 

Not yet... if only there were a marine biologist here. 

"The sea was angry that day, my friends.  Like an old man trying to send back soup at a deli."

@Paul 

Fortunately, I am very much up on modern poop culture.

And you misspelled "wrappers", leaving the "w" out.  How do you struggle with wrappers?  Difficult to tear cleanly?

@Tim 

Thanks! That sounds... Very weird, decadent and unnecessary like something the Western Ancient Roman artistocracy may have done as their empire was crumbling around them ca. 470 AD.

Hacks! That's such a great show. Either I don't recall DINNER THEATER featuring on it (and my memory is beyond bad, so it's likely), or it was in season 3, which I have not seen yet.

@Andrzej 
dinner theater is (or perhaps was) absolutely a thing in the u.s. take it from one who, in his salad days, once doubled as an actor/waiter…or perhaps it was the other way around…memory conveniently fails at this hour and this age.
the nearest version close to you might be the 9 pm show at www.chaton.com. but i don’t actually see anything quite as comparable in warsaw.

@Steve L I don't think those poor mountaineers had time or energy for recreational climbing. 

Hey, I just got a surprise. I expected that "a native or inhabitant of a mountainous region" would be an archaic definition, but M-W has it as the first definition, followed by "a person who climbs mountains for sport."

(Not to be confused with "sport climbing." Jeez, all these usages get confusing.)

@Eric Hougland 

Strangely, Kojak was a huge hit on Polish TV in the 1970s, and it had many reruns, also popular, including the one I watched in the 90s. I wonder what decided that the pre-1989 censors allowed this particular series to air behind the iron curtain...

My mom had a major crush on Telly Savalas because of Kojak 🤣

@Andrzej 

That's interesting about Kojak. I wouldn't have ever guessed that.

Thanks.

@Caroline Kearney 
We hadalittle book with charming illustrations (the tiger chasing around and beginning to melt!) but I have no idea what became of it.  I was very young, and 'Sambo' seemed no more odd than our neighbors named Chiatakis or Saint Clair....  
it wd be difficult to find  now.

@Darcey O’D 

I look up some proper nouns and trivia, so you have to take that into account, but I agree with you. In recent weeks puzzle difficulty has become unpredictable. This week Tuesday took me 21 minutes, and Friday 15.

IMO Mr Fagliano's editing was much more consistent.

@RNR 
"*how to tell an old newbie from an old oldie? In my case, when the concern is one of completion, not timing."

Everyone solves in their own fashion, but I--who consider myself, if not an oldie, a middle-agie--I still like to take time, linger, and savor, especially on late week puzzles. And even on Mon. and Tues., I'm often too groggy for effective speed solving.

@Elsie Borden - my best friend in those days (the 70s) was the younger sister of the Nitty Gritty’s keyboard player. I never think of them without recalling Bush the Elder…

<a href="https://politico.com/story/2018/12/01/george-hw-bush-death-presidency-life-legacy-1037038" target="_blank">https://politico.com/story/2018/12/01/george-hw-bush-death-presidency-life-legacy-1037038</a>

And, yes, I had occasions to perform for and meet him; inept, of a befuddled and misguided political mindset, yet - a real human being. Nearly a mensch. The apples really can fall far from the tree, especially with the help of carrion fowl.

