@David Connell 

The books (Complete Lachlan, Walking Types) are very, very different from the blog, and very much aimed at Scottish hillwalkers. I do know a few Americans who've enjoyed them, despite the Scots dialogue and Gaelic toponyms, but very much caveat lector on that.
There is a print-on-demand physical edition that combines both ebooks, but it's a UK-based company, and postage is probably prohibitive. (I made no effort to maintain a US outlet, since interest was predictably slight).

